// @check
// @error undeclared B
// KNOWN-REMAINING — xfail (ROADMAP A11: "mutual recursion across *separate*
// `type` decls" is listed as REMAINING). This program is SOUND and SHOULD
// compile, but currently errors because a forward reference between two mutually
// recursive `type` aliases is not resolved. NOT a silent compiler fix — captured
// as a "should-compile-but-errors" xfail.
//
// THE GAP: `type A` references `B` before `B` is declared. Self-reference within
// ONE alias works (types/recursive-tree.vl, recursive-type-build-traverse.vl),
// but a cycle that spans two aliases is not collected up-front, so resolving
// `A.b`'s `B` fails with "undeclared B" instead of tying the rec-group across
// both declarations.
//
// EXPECTED: both aliases resolve into one rec-group and this compiles clean.
// ACTUAL: `Syntax error: undeclared B`.
//
// TODO(A11): pre-register all top-level `type` names before resolving any body,
// so a forward/mutual reference between alias bodies is legal. When fixed, flip
// this to `// @run` and assert traversal output.
type A = { b: B | null }
type B = { a: A | null }
let x: A = { b: { a: null } }
print(0)
